Sentencas: Methane-fueled thin film micro-solid oxide fuel cells (mu SOFCs) based on palladium (Pd) anodes are discussed in this article.
Titulo: Methane-fueled thin film micro-solid oxide fuel cells with nanoporous palladium anodes

Sentencas: The mu SOFCs are composed of porous platinum (Pt) cathodes, 8 mol.%yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) ultrathin electrolytes, and Pd anodes - specifically, a Pt/YSZ/Pd heterostructure synthesized by physical vapor deposition.
Titulo: Methane-fueled thin film micro-solid oxide fuel cells with nanoporous palladium anodes

Sentencas: The Pt/YSZ/Pd mu SOFCs exhibit a power density of 385 mW cm(-2) and an open circuit voltage of 0.77 V at 550 degrees C. A detailed study on synthesis, microstructure and functional properties of the nanoporous Pd films is presented.
Titulo: Methane-fueled thin film micro-solid oxide fuel cells with nanoporous palladium anodes

Sentencas: Possible anodic methane reactions, carbon deposition on Pd anodes, and carbon suppression approaches are discussed.
Titulo: Methane-fueled thin film micro-solid oxide fuel cells with nanoporous palladium anodes

Sentencas: The results are of potential relevance to advancing low temperature micro-fuel cell technology using hydrocarbon fuels.
Titulo: Methane-fueled thin film micro-solid oxide fuel cells with nanoporous palladium anodes
